  "short description": "Production-ready workflow engine with 43+ control-flow patterns for enterprise business process automation",
  "long description": "YAWL (Yet Another Workflow Language) is a powerful BPM/Workflow engine built on formal foundations in Petri Net theory. Trusted by enterprises worldwide for mission-critical business process automation.\n\n**Key Features:**\n- 43+ Workflow Control-Flow Patterns (WCP) implemented\n- Petri Net-based execution with formal verification\n- Human and non-human resource management\n- Dynamic process adaptation via Worklets\n- Real-time process monitoring and analytics\n- Calendar-based task scheduling\n- Cost tracking and budgeting\n- Multi-tenant architecture\n\n**Supported Patterns Include:**\n- Sequence, Parallel Split, Synchronization\n- Exclusive Choice, Multi-Choice, Discriminator\n- N-out-of-M, Deferred Choice, Interleaved Routing\n- Milestone, Critical Section, Structured Loop\n- Cancellation patterns (activity, case, region)\n- Data transformation and accumulation\n\n**Integration Options:**\n- REST API (Interface A/B/E/X)\n- Web-based administration console\n- Custom worklist handlers\n- External resource allocation\n\n**Deployment:**\n- Fully managed containers on Azure Kubernetes Service\n- Multi-zone high availability\n- Automatic scaling based on workload\n- GDPR and SOC 2 compliant\n- Azure AD integration for single sign-on",
